# Git Workflow

- Do NOT run `git add`, `git commit`, `git push`, or any other git write operations unless the user explicitly asks
- The developer prefers to handle all git work (staging, committing, pushing) themselves in the terminal
- It's fine to run read-only git commands (`git status`, `git log`, `git diff`) when needed for context
